x4freetext: Natural high purity metallic Pt foils
consisting of Al (50 um), Pt (49.0 um) foils
irradiated with 50 MeV deuteron beam of 70 nA 1h.
The beam intensity was adopted from the monitor
The Al foils served for monitoring the beam, as energy
absorber and as catcher foils to stop the recoiled
Activity of the foils was measured several times to
Several series of spectra were recorded.
Decay data were taken from NUDAT2.6 online database.
Energy degradation was calculated by using the semi
empirical formula of Andersen and Ziegler.
